  "title": "SSH option injection via dash-prefixed target in parseSSHTarget",
  "description": "The parseSSHTarget function accepts any string as an SSH target without validating that the host does not start with a dash. The parsed host is appended directly to the SSH argument list without a -- separator, allowing a target like -oProxyCommand=calc to be interpreted as an SSH flag and execute arbitrary commands on the local machine.",
